      <textAnnotation id="sid-5142449E-CE8F-4199-A6C9-1C1383926255" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Process Tower: Procure To Pay
Process Group: Logistics Management Inbound
Process: LI-200-050 Bill Supplier for Rework
</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-A04B020C-0C61-4687-8E95-CF92AAA00727" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Determine if the rework or repair costs should be borne by the supplier?</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-487C245C-BABF-4DA4-A936-0DA415A901CA" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>The Prices in Rework or Repair POs
* Entered manually as per alignment with supplier via quotations
* Automatically flows from OA or PIR</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-1EF6CF46-739E-4245-9079-13890C6930E8" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Required if third party supplier performs the service onsite</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-55234D32-066C-42F6-9F13-C5DA722A10BC" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Billing Process Steps -
1. Determine whether the rework or repair costs should be borne by the supplier based on warranty terms, purchase agreements and original purchase orders.
2. Calculate all the costs associated with the rework or repair, including materials, labor, and any additional inspections.
3. Notify supplier of the rework or repair costs and align to receive credit invoice for the rework or repair services.
5. If rework or repair is performed by a third- party supplier on-site, a service PO with repair or rework costs to be utilized.</text>
      </textAnnotation>
